text: Elaine Symons (born 4 December 1974) is an Irish actress, who trained at the Royal Academy of Dramatic Art. She is best known for her role as alcoholic mother-of-five Rose Kelly in the BBC One school-based drama series Waterloo Road, which she played from 2009 to 2011. ==Other websites== * Category:1974 births Category:Living people Category:Irish television actors Category:Irish movie actors Category:Irish stage actors Category:Alumni of the Royal Academy of Dramatic Art
